On Religious Freedom Day, the President of the United States proclaims the importance of defending the fundamental principles of religious liberty. The proclamation highlights the diversity of religious and non-religious backgrounds in America and emphasizes the shared commitment to liberty. It acknowledges that religious freedom strengthens the nation and recognizes the contributions of faith communities throughout history. The proclamation also addresses the need to protect religious freedom and speaks out against religious bias and hate crimes. It calls for unity and rejects divisive politics that target people based on their religion. The proclamation extends beyond the United States and emphasizes the universal and inalienable right to religious liberty. The President calls on Americans to commemorate Religious Freedom Day and work towards protecting this right for future generations.